Holy symbols are representations of [[deities|deity]] or other ideals of a particular [[religion]], used as [[magical implement]]s by wielders of [[divine magic]]. A holy symbol might be an amulet depicting a symbol of the faith, an engraving on a shield, a tiny box holding a fragment of a sacred relic, or any number of objects that hold sacred meaning.

